list.item:
If it is known that there is going to be a Summit Meeting, then the
                        meeting of Foreign Ministers is more likely to produce some useful
                        results;

The Russians would have no incentive to precipitate a crisis if a Summit
                        Meeting was fixed, and world opinion would be against them if they started
                        something in the meantime;

If, on the contrary, no date had been fixed for a Summit it would be in
                        their interest to start something precisely in order to force us to a Summit
                        under the pressure of a crisis;
